  <!-- FAQ -->
  <div class="container u-space-1 mb-9">
    <div class="w-md-80 w-lg-50 text-center mx-auto">
      <div class="mb-9">
        <span class="u-label u-label--sm u-label--primary mb-2">FAQ</span>
        <h2 class="text-codefund-purple">Common 
          <span class="font-weight-bold text-codefund-green">Questions</span>
        </h2>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div id="FAQCollapse" class="accordion">
      <!-- Card -->
      <div class="card u-card-collapse">
        <div class="card-header px-4" id="FAQHeadingOne">
          <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#FAQOne" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="FAQOne" role="button">
            <h3 class="h6 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center font-weight-normal u-card-collapse__heading mb-0">
              Does my website qualify?
              <span class="fa fa-angle-up u-card-collapse__heading-icon"></span>
            </h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="FAQOne" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="FAQHeadingOne" data-parent="#FAQCollapse">
          <div class="card-body px-4">
            <p>
              We are very selective when it comes to websites that can participate with CodeFund. The website:
              <ul class="list-unstyled" style="color: #77838f;">
                <li><i class="fal fa-check text-codefund-green"></i> must be serving the developer community, whether as API docs, blogs, applications or other.</li>
                <li><i class="fal fa-check text-codefund-green"></i> must not be a pay-to-use application.</li>
                <li><i class="fal fa-check text-codefund-green"></i> must receive at least 5,000 unique visitors per month.</li>
              </ul>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- End Card -->

      <!-- Card -->
      <div class="card u-card-collapse">
        <div class="card-header px-4" id="FAQHeadingTwo">
          <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#FAQTwo" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="FAQTwo" role="button">
            <h3 class="h6 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center font-weight-normal u-card-collapse__heading mb-0">
              How much money can I make?
              <span class="fa fa-angle-up u-card-collapse__heading-icon"></span>
            </h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="FAQTwo" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="FAQHeadingTwo" data-parent="#FAQCollapse">
          <div class="card-body px-4">
            <p>The earnings vary based on the website and advertisers willing to spend money on it. Typically we see around a $3.50 CPM (cost per 1,000 impressions). Average earnings per 1,000 impressions is around $1.75 but can fluctuate based on advertiser demand.</p>
            <p>For example, a moderately popular website with 500,000 ad impressions per month at a $3.50 CPM would generate anywhere between $875 and $1,200/month.</p>
            <p>We typically start publishers at a 50% split on gross revenue. We do pay out higher percentage rates based on the quantity and quality of traffic the website generates.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- End Card -->

      <!-- Card -->
      <div class="card u-card-collapse">
        <div class="card-header px-4" id="FAQHeadingThree">
          <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#FAQThree" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="FAQThree" role="button">
            <h3 class="h6 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center font-weight-normal u-card-collapse__heading mb-0">
              Why should I use you over Carbon Ads?
              <span class="fa fa-angle-up u-card-collapse__heading-icon"></span>
            </h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="FAQThree" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="FAQHeadingThree" data-parent="#FAQCollapse">
          <div class="card-body px-4">
            <p>
              Here are some differences between them and us:
              <ul class="list-unstyled" style="color: #77838f;">
                <li><i class="fal fa-check text-codefund-green"></i> We follow the <%= link "ethical advertisement", to: page_path(@conn, :ethical_advertising) %> method of advertising.</li>
                <li><i class="fal fa-check text-codefund-green"></i> We are an <a href="https://github.com/gitcoinco/codefund">open source platform</a>. You can see exactly how it all works.</li>
                <li><i class="fal fa-check text-codefund-green"></i> We pay up to 70% of all gross revenue back to the publisher.</li>
                <li><i class="fal fa-check text-codefund-green"></i> We are not owned and run by BuySellAds.com</li>
              </ul>
            </p>
            <p>
              We think <a href="https://carbonads.net" target="_blank">Carbon Ads</a> is a wonderful company. They have helped so many projects generate revenue through advertising.
              We just approach funding the developer community a little differently.
            </p>
            <p>
              We do have some publishers using both CodeFund and Carbon Ads. Let us know if that's something you are interested in doing.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- End Card -->

      <!-- Card -->
      <div class="card u-card-collapse">
        <div class="card-header px-4" id="FAQHeadingFour">
          <div class="collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" data-target="#FAQFour" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="FAQFour" role="button">
            <h3 class="h6 d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center font-weight-normal u-card-collapse__heading mb-0">
              Can I have the distributions deposited to Open Collective?
              <span class="fa fa-angle-up u-card-collapse__heading-icon"></span>
            </h3>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div id="FAQFour" class="collapse" aria-labelledby="FAQHeadingFour" data-parent="#FAQCollapse">
          <div class="card-body px-4">
            <p>Absolutely. We work closely with the team at <a href="https://opencollective.com" target="_blank">Open Collective</a>
            and are happy to send any earnings directly into your collective.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <!-- End Card -->
    </div>
  </div>
  <!-- END FAQ -->

